Package com.cafean.jobstream.common.util

Class AbstractModuleLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.jobstream.common.util.AbstractModuleLoader
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnimationModuleLoader, CJFImporterLoader, ClientTrackerModuleLoader, JobImporterLoader, NumericDataSourceLoader, NumericFunctionLoader, PlatformModuleLoader, VersionControlLoader
    public abstract class AbstractModuleLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the base class of each of the module loaders. It provides a set of utility methods that are used by each of the extending classes to determine what modules are available. It also provides utilities for loading these classes.

    • Method Detail

      • getJarNames

        public static java.lang.String[] getJarNames​(java.io.File folder)
        Returns a String array of filenames in the directory which are potential plug-in and/or module files.

        This method opens and examines the Manifest of each of the JAR files in the given folder to ensure that the Load-Priority and Load-Name attributes are properly honored by all Job Stream related module loaders.

        The Load-Priority attribute indicates that modules with a larger priority number should be loaded (i.e. added to the search path) after modules with a smaller priority number. If no priority is provided then priority 1 (i.e. "first") is assumed.

        The Load-Name attribute indicates that the module is mutually exclusive with other modules that have the same Load-Name and only one should be included. The load priority of each module is used to determine which of the mutually exclusive modules should be used.

        Parameters:
        folder - a File referring to the directory to iterate through

      • getBaseFolder

        public final java.io.File getBaseFolder()

      • isStreamSupportEnabled

        public static boolean isStreamSupportEnabled()
        Returns true if stream support is enabled for this SNAP installation as defined by the value of the com.cafean.jobstream.enabled property in the file [SNAP Install]/bin/snap.prop. If the property is present and set to false then job stream support is considered disabled for this SNAP installation. If it is not present or it is set to some other value then job stream support is considered enabled for this SNAP installation.
        Returns:
        true if stream support is enabled
